Vulcan, the Disaster


02 Jul 2019 16:00





~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Dondelinger:  Now, I'm going to burn this donut to show you how many calories it has.

Homer:  NOOOOOOOOOOO!

Dondelinger:  The bright blue flame indicates this was a particularly sweet donut.

Homer:  This is not happening! This can not be happening

 The Simpsons, October 14, 1993.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

EDIT:  250 upvotes in a month. Thank you so much everyone. I hope I can keep writing articles you enjoy!

My third article, after Stalled Conversation. This one is a bit more heavy.

YOUSPOILERS?

...fine...


The foundation contain a Volcano God for 3/4ths of a century with organic food, until by accident this being gets a taste for junk food, and demands more. Over time, it gets bigger, lazier, and less threatening, until it's not even a true threat, so long as we keep giving it the  containment regimen.




This was also my first foray with listpages, which alone makes it the most labor-intensive article I've written. It's also had the most reviews, revisions, and re-writes, but I think it was worth it!

Image sources are here, all under the Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 Unported license, or Pixbay free use license.

All locations (Moaha Island) and names within this article are works of fiction.

